CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 6, 1953, pg. 6, reads: "Bapt. Women Hold One-Day Institute - The first Leadership Institute of the Baptist Missionary Women was held Monday in Central Baptist Church. The program was climaxed at night when Mrs. Uvee Mdodana Arbouin was guest speaker.  Pictured, left to right: Mrs. B. R. Hairston, Mrs. Estelle Blanks, Mrs. L. B. Mosely, Mrs. Arbouin, Mrs. Corinne Moses, president of the Western District Auxiliary; Mrs. Edith Whitaker Taylor and Mrs. J. H. Robinson. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left, Mrs. B. R. Hairston, Estelle Blanks, Mrs. L. B. Mosely, Uvee Mdodana Arbouin, Corinne Moses, Edith Whitaker Taylor, and Mrs. J. H. Robinson, posed in Central Baptist Church
